Note, my current device (Nexus 6P) is officially unsupported(yet?) but the issues stated here also plagued my Nexus 5 which was not unsupported.  I've never had issues with the app itself regarding calls, quality, or performance. My main issue is when I'm not using the app. It has a persistent never-ending notification keeping me signed in long after I've ended my call. The app itself has no apparent way to prevent this and the solution I've found is to actually remove it from my recent apps list. This is far from intuitive and not in line with most app standards. The huge flaw is that it consumes battery at an alarming rate. I've had a full charge drop to 50% in 4 hours because I forgot to kill the app. I would like a setting to prevent persistence or some intelligence in the app to background itself properly. I'll gladly adjust my review when that is remedied.
